# Basic session

This scenario creates several plain tmux sessions with no repo metadata and
then launches `sesh`.

    :bins jj cat

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', and 'cat' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :t new-session -d -s alpha "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s beta "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s gamma "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 80 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0

This snapshot shows the initial picker state before any query is typed, so it
should list all discovered tmux sessions.

    :snap

```terminal
session:
  5/5 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close
▌⬤ alpha                                                                       ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

![light](basic-session.md.snap.1.light.svg)
![dark](basic-session.md.snap.1.dark.svg)

This snapshot shows the picker after typing `bet`, so the selection should move
to the `beta` session.

    :k bet
    :snap

```terminal
session: bet
  1/5 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-n] new | [C-x] close
▌⬤ beta                                                                        ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

![light](basic-session.md.snap.2.light.svg)
![dark](basic-session.md.snap.2.dark.svg)

